00:07:57,044 --> 00:07:58,777
for all these years.            

227
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:00,244
 That's outstanding.            

228
00:08:00,246 --> 00:08:02,047
That little underlying tone     
   of the molasses              

229
00:08:02,049 --> 00:08:04,248
and the brown sugar --          
        mmm.                    

230
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,984
     Great roll,                
onion crunch makes it,          

231
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,184
  little old-school             
     mayonnaise,                

232
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:09,320
and iceberg lettuce --          
   takes you back.              

233
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:14,125
But when you get brined,        
tender meat inside of ground,   

234
00:08:14,127 --> 00:08:18,463
super-flavorful, textural meat, 
 you can't beat it.             

235
00:08:18,465 --> 00:08:20,332
        Bologna sandwich.       

236
00:08:20,334 --> 00:08:21,866
                I'm not even    
              a fan of bologna, 

237
00:08:21,868 --> 00:08:23,335
               but I come here  
         just for this sandwich.

238
00:08:23,337 --> 00:08:25,069
   Best bologna I've ever had   
           in my life.          

239
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:26,337
      SMITH: Plating ribs.      

240
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,072
      We're in a city full      
         of restaurants,        

241
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:31,075
   and this is one of the ones  
 you want to come back to over, 

242
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:32,477
            and over            
         and over again.        

243
00:08:32,479 --> 00:08:35,947
You make 900 square-feet        
